title: Caitlyn Jenner's 'I Am Cait' Officially Renewed for Season 2
text:
Comments The docu-series about the former 'Keeping Up with the Kardashians' star will return next year for another season. 
" I Am Cait " is returning for the second season. The docu-series focusing Caitlyn Jenner 's life after her transformation has been picked up by E! for another cycle. "I'm looking forward to continuing the conversation," the reality TV star says. "Caitlyn's story has ignited a global conversation on the transgender community on a scale that has never been seen before," says E! EVP, programming and development, Jeff Olde. "We are honored Caitlyn has chosen to continue to share her ongoing evolution with our viewers around the world." "I Am Cait" debuted on July 26, 2015 to 2.73 million viewers but dipped in its ratings following the premiere. It featured her family from " Keeping Up With the Kardashians ". The upcoming season is expected to air next year.
